article.headline: Kent State 63, Akron 57
article.story: KENT, Ohio (AP) -- Mike Scott's layup with 11:30 to play started a 6-0 run that rallied Kent State to a 63-57 victory over Akron on Saturday. The Golden Flashes (16-6, 10-1 MAC) took over first place in the Mid-American Conference East Division with the win. After trailing most of the way, Scott tied the game at 45, while Akron went seven minutes without a field goal. Armon Gates hit a free throw, and Nate Gerwig converted three to complete the run. Dru Joyce had 17 points for Akron (16-5, 9-2), and Romeo Travis had 13. Kevin Warzynski finished with 15 points for Kent State, and Jay Youngblood had 14. After leading 35-30 at halftime, Akron was held to 22 points on 30 percent shooting in the second half. Kent State has won three straight, and stopped Akron's winning string at three.
